    <h1>TALKS</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200814/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-14"><time>2020-08-14</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Next In Fash­ion</p>
    <p>Hosted by train­ing com­pany Gen­eral Assem­bly, this talk fea­tures home-grown busi­ness own­ers in­clud­ing Ms Raena Lim, co-founder of Style The­ory, a fash­ion plat­form pro­mot­ing a smarter way to con­sume fash­ion; Mr Afzal Im­ram, co-founder of State Prop­erty, a con­tem­po­rary fine jew­ellery la­bel; and Ms Megha Singh, men­tor­ship and match pro­gramme direc­tor of Crib, a non-profit so­cial en­ter­prise that helps women set up suc­cess­ful busi­nesses. They will speak about how far the lo­cal fash­ion in­dus­try has come, what is ahead and how tech­nol­ogy is shap­ing the in­dus­try.</p>
    <p>WHEN: To­day, 12.30 - 1.30pm</p>
    <p>INFO: Free with regis­tra­tion, watch it at str.sg/JhNr</p>
    <p>Scal­ing Ac­tion On Sus­tain­abil­ity</p>
    <p>The talk, hosted by train­ing com­pany Gen­eral Assem­bly, fea­tures ad­vo­cates of eco-friendly life­styles. They in­clude Mr David Ward, founder of The Nur­tur­ing Co and a leader in sus­tain­able prod­uct busi­ness de­vel­op­ment; keynote speaker and change maker Veer­ap­pan Swami­nathan, founder and direc­tor of Sus­tain­able Liv­ing Lab, which de­vel­ops in­no­va­tive so­lu­tions for or­gan­i­sa­tions and com­mu­ni­ties that want to grow sus­tain­ably; and Ms Sam Shu Qin, co-founder of Our Sin­ga­pore Reefs, which con­nects like-minded marine en­thu­si­asts through div­ing and ed­u­ca­tional outreach pro­grammes.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Mon, 6.30 - 7.30pm</p>
    <p>INFO: Free with regis­tra­tion, watch it at str.sg/JhNF</p>
    <p>WSG Ca­reers Con­nect On The Go</p>
    <p>Or­gan­ised by Work­force Sin­ga­pore, the event al­lows par­tic­i­pants to con­nect with ca­reer coaches who can help them dis­cover their strengths and make in­formed de­ci­sions about their ca­reer and goals.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Sengkang Pub­lic Li­brary, Com­pass One, 1 Sengkang Square MRT: Sengkang WHEN: Wed - Fri</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION: Free INFO: wsg.gov.sg/ca­reer-ser­vices</p>


